# Studio global playback (steel standard)

One player system for all studio audio. **Do not fork per page.**

## Modules (only these)

| Role | Module |
|------|--------|
| Markup + script list SSOT | `shared/studio-playback-stack.js` (`BurnfolderStudioPlaybackStack`) |
| Shell, engine, bar mount | `studio/js/studio-playback-shell.js` |
| Play API | `studio/js/stream-player.js` (`BurnfolderStreamPlayer`) |
| Now-playing bridge | `studio/js/stream-now-playing.js` |
| Engine | `shared/mux-playback.js` |
| Bar UI | `shared/now-playing-bar.js` |
| Row tap (coarse pointer) | `shared/studio-tap.js` |

## Required on every playback-capable page

### 1. Mux CDN (defer, `<head>`)

```html
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mux/mux-player" defer></script>
```

### 2. Script order (sequential — never parallel-load stream scripts)

```
shared/studio-playback-stack.js   ← MUST load before studio-playback-shell.js
→ … PLAYBACK_CORE from stack …
→ studio-playback-shell.js
→ stream-player.js
→ stream-now-playing.js
→ page script
```

`BurnfolderStudioPlaybackStack.CORE_SCRIPTS` is the canonical list. SPA router `PLAYBACK_CORE` must stay in sync.

### 3. Global shell markup

**Never** `createElement('mux-player')` for `#activeMuxPlayer`.

Shell is injected once via `BurnfolderStudioPlaybackStack.ensureShellMarkup()` — a real `<mux-player>` tag in markup (parsed before defer upgrades it). Static HTML copy optional; stack inject is the SSOT.

IDs (global only — do not reuse in preview UIs):

- `#studioGlobalPlayback` — shell wrapper
- `#activeMuxPlayer` — global audio element
- `#bottomBar`, `#streamNowPlayingTitle`, `#streamPlayPause`, `#streamNowPlayingClose`

Entry editor preview uses **separate** IDs inside `.studio-preview-player`: `previewMuxPlayer`, `previewBottomBar`, etc. Global dedupe must **never** steal preview nodes.

## Click-to-play (music list)

Per-row binding at build time in `stream-page.js` — `wireTrackRowPlay(row)`:

- **Desktop:** plain `click` on each `.music-track-row`
- **Coarse pointer:** `BurnfolderTouchTap.bind(row, …)`
- After play: `nudgeMuxPlay(playbackId)` in the same click turn
- **Start by `playbackId`**, never DOM/group index alone — `playQueue` remaps after filtering videos via `startPlaybackId`
- **Do not** rewrite `#activeMuxPlayer` on `pointerdown` prime — prefetch only (`BurnfolderPlaybackPrefetch`)

Never list-delegation alone for row play.

## Shell invariants (do not break)

1. **`stream-now-playing.js`** — init through shell first; never `if (!bottomBar) return` before shell mount
2. **`syncAfterNavigation`** — updates bar state only; **never** calls `mountBar()` (recursion → stack overflow)
3. **`customElements.upgrade(player)`** when `player.play` missing, before async `whenDefined`
4. SPA: `#studioGlobalPlayback` persists at `body` level; `#studio-spa-content` swaps page content only

## SPA bootstrap

Every SPA entry page (`index`, `dashboard`, `stream`, `video`, `journal`, `ideas`, `releases`, `word-pull`, `stream-song`, `stream-album`) must load `studio-playback-stack.js` + `studio-spa-router.js`.

`studio-spa-router.js` prepends `PLAYBACK_CORE` to lazy script loads so SPA nav always has `BurnfolderStreamPlayer`. Script dedupe keys by **pathname** (absolute vs relative URLs must not re-inject playback modules — that restarts audio).

Song/album hubs are soft-SPA: never hard-navigate them while audio is playing.

## Inline / preview players (allowed, separate)

- Visible video: `stream-shared.createMuxVideoPlayer()`
- Designer heroes: `song-page-render.js`, `album-page-render.js`
- Entry preview: `.studio-preview-player` with `previewMuxPlayer` id
- Prefetch: `playback-prefetch.js` hidden element

These must **not** use `#activeMuxPlayer` unless inside `#studioGlobalPlayback`.

## New studio page checklist

1. Add mux CDN defer in head
2. Load `studio-playback-stack.js` before `studio-playback-shell.js`
3. Load full `CORE_SCRIPTS` (or rely on SPA router if SPA page)
4. Before first user play: `shell.ensureShell()` + `shell.mountBar()` + `shell.getEngine()`
5. Play via `BurnfolderStreamPlayer.playItem` / `playQueue` or shell engine directly
6. Bump `?v=` cache on touched scripts

  ## Regression check

1. Hard refresh `/studio/stream.html` — songs load, no stack error
2. Click track → bottom bar + audio
3. SPA: dashboard → music → journal → ideas — **audio must keep playing without restart**
4. Soft-nav into `stream-song` / `stream-album` — audio continues
5. Entry editor preview bar still independent from global shell
6. Public site: play on audio → soft-nav to song/album hub — audio continues